ard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=804.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Birth of a Paladin: Continued</span><hr size=1> Tamazar had been at a full run.  He was extremely tired as he entered the church and knelt before the High Priest in front of him.  &quot;Father, I have been on a journey to the great lands outside of Felwithe.&quot; Tamazar's breathing began to slow as the Priest placed his hand on his shoulder.<br>
<br>
&quot;What did you see on your journey?&quot; asked the priest.<br>
<br>
Tamazar quickly replied, &quot;While my journey was not long, I did see many creatures.  Giant Wasps and Bats littered the landscape, and I occasionally saw skeletons of fallen elves walking as if they were alive.&quot;  Here, the young elf paused.  He removed his pack and pulled out his notebook.  He turned to the page with the drawing that his quill had so perfectly made, showed it to the priest and continued.  &quot;This, Father, is why I returned so soon.  I saw two of these creatures, and they did not speak in the elven tongue.  I could not understand anything they said as they ran towards me.  They were quite weak however, and my mace and short sword quickly dispatched both of them.&quot;  Tamazar went on, &quot;Before it died however, one of the creatures managed to slice open my arm.  When I noticed the gash, I placed my hand over it to stop the bleeding, and instantly, the wound disappeared.  Not even a scar remained.&quot;<br>
<br>
The priest looked at the drawing and began speaking.  &quot;The creatures you met, my son, are Orcs of the Clan of Crushbone.  They were probably scouts send by the Emperor to find a good target for their next raid.  I praise you for killing them as quickly as you did, orcs are quite strong.  You shall be honored at our next mass for dispatching the vile beasts.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What about my injury, Father?&quot;, asked Tamazar.<br>
<br>
&quot;My son, you are the first Elf I have ever seen with the powers you have described.  I have heard of Humans and Dwarves with the same ability to heal themselves.  I believe you are a Paladin.  In due time, you will be granted the powers of the High Priests as well.  You must use your skills wisely, as you can save the lives of both yourself, and your comrades in battle.  Your ability to heal yourself can only be used once a day however, and will completely heal you of any injuries you have sustained.  Use it wisely.&quot;<br>
<br>
The priest walked towards the altar with Tamazar at his side.  He picked up a piece of parchment and his quill.  As he spoke, the quill wrote, &quot;My dear Drazen Agestim, Master Tailor of Felwithe.  We have in our midst the first and only Paladin to be born within our city walls.  Please create for him a garment that will be recognized throughout Norrath to show Tamazar Fleethart's stature.  He shall be honored at the next mass as the first Paladin of Tunare.  Signed, Quintane Solen, High Priest of Tunare.&quot;<br>
<br>
He gave the rolled parchment to Tamazar and instructed him to go to the tailor's shop on the east side of the city.  Tamazar knelt before the priest in reverence and went on his way.  He went directly to the tailor's shop and handed the note to Drazen Agestim.  Dragen read the words on the parchment, nodded, and began instructing his assistants to find the highest quality silks and fabrics they could find.  &quot;Return in two days time young man, and your garment will be finished.&quot;, said Drazen, and Tamazar left the shop without a word.  He was very excited to tell his parents of the news he had received, although he didn't quite understand the possibilities and quests his future had in store for him.<br>
<br>
When he arrived at his small home in North Felwithe, he was greeted by his parents.  &quot;Mother, Father!!!  I have great news.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What is it, my son?&quot;, replied his father.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am a Paladin.  The priest told me I am the first and only Paladin to ever be born in Felwithe.  I have the power to heal myself and others.  The priest is having something made for me at the tailor's shop and blessing me at the next Mass.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That is outstanding news!&quot;, replied his mother, and she hugged him before she finished speaking.  &quot;I will make a great feast.  We will eat heartily tonight.&quot;, and eat they did.  Tamazar was so full, that after dinner, he went straight to bed, and slept until the sun rose the next morning. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usadelia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sadelia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/31/01 5:41:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=804.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~pamalam/_uimages/kitty.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Birth of a Paladin: Continued</span><hr size=1> good story! <p><table border="0" width="545" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
