     People all around him were talking to him, staring in amazement, and just plain being friendly as he walked down the streets of Felwithe.  He stopped to pet his friend's wolf puppy, and continued on his way.  It was about thirty minutes before he saw the shop, since he had walked so slowly and stopped to talk to many people.  He noticed the shop was still closed, but the candles inside were still alive with light.  He calmly sat down and waited, hiding his excitement about what would happen later in the day.<br>
     The shop keeper opened the door promptly at 7am, and Tamazar shuffled in quickly.  Before him, the Tailor's assistant held a beautiful robe with a winged heart embriodered in the center, the mark of his family for over forty centuries.  As everyone knows, elves live a very long time, some well into their fifth and sixth centuries.  Tamazar was 50 years old, and not even half finished with all his training in the fine arts of Elven Fighting.  The assistant broght the robe to Tamazar and placed it over his head.  He then went back into the rear of the shop and returned with a heavy belt that was placed around Tamazar's waist.  He looked like a heavenly knight, he noticed as he gazed at himself in the mirror for a moment.  He realized that it was now 8am and he had to get back home.  He removed the robes and belt, handed them back to the assistant, and started his short run home after thanking the Tailor.  The tailor promised him the cloak would be done before the day's mass started.<br>
